# Next.js Task Management Frontend

A task management frontend application built with Next.js. It connects to a backend API to perform CRUD operations, provides filtering options, and uses a modal interface for creating and editing tasks.

---

## Features

- **Server-Side Rendering (SSR)** for enhanced performance and SEO using `getServerSideProps`.
- **Dynamic Routes** for task details and editing tasks.
- **Task Management**: Create, read, update, and delete tasks via a modern UI.
- **Filter Tasks**: Filter tasks by status (`pending`, `inprogress`, `completed`).
- **Responsive Design**: Fully responsive layout using Tailwind CSS.
- **Modal Interface**: Interactive modals for creating and editing tasks.

---

## Prerequisites

- **Node.js** (v14 or later)
- A running instance of the backend API. Ensure the [Node.js Task Management API](https://github.com/mansoor1025/task-management-backend) is set up and running.

